While the concept itself is fun, I feel the article tries to cram multiple elements together at an unnatural pace. You have the consoles, the demonic entities, and a hole in Dan Dunn's basement. None of these are fleshed out, and they're all introduced at breakneck speed. There's some tonal issues as well. From what I can tell, the demonic entities are separate from SCP-5116-A, but I can't discern that from the text. In fact, I didn't even realize it until I was near the end of the article. It's tightly written, but it doesn't work with what's trying to be done. Delving a little more into the history and purpose behind the anomaly, even just a tiny bit, would've worked wonders for the piece.

-1, unfortunately







